  <summary date="2007-03-12T21:55:30Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Stop Arming Iran Act - Prohibits the Department of Defense (DOD) from selling any parts for the F-14 fighter aircraft (parts), whether through the Defense Reutilization and Marketing Service or through another DOD agency or element.

Provides an exception with respect to the sale of such parts to a U.S. museum or similar organization involved in the preservation of F-14 fighter aircraft for historical purposes.

Prohibits the issuance of any license for the export of such parts to a non-U.S. person or entity.</summary>
